raw_data.title: Program Manager
raw_data.description:
The Program Manager ensures successful performance, cost, and scheduling for the most efficient and effective completion of contract work. The Program Manager will generally serve as the primary point of contact for the government team, as well as any subcontractors. Leads planning, scheduling, monitoring, and reporting activities for
projects.

raw_data.title: Solutions Architect
raw_data.description: Develops the architecture and design of IT software solutions. Assists with various highly complex tasks on the project, working as needed to keep the team on track and ahead of schedule. Develops complex data integrations, very complex customizations and other tasks that are needed as part of project execution.

raw_data.title: Jr. Developer
raw_data.description: Captures/documents requirements, performs configurations specified by the Architect or Senior Developer, facilites meetings with users. Facilitates and conducts training, facilitates user testing, and performs testing.

raw_data.title: Sr. Developer
raw_data.description: Manages technical tasks on the project, oversees the design, build and testing of the solution. Also performs services related to configuration, development, and testing of the application.
